-- Nordea appoints new head of its Danish division
-- 
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 04:57AM EDT
-- None



COPENHAGEN, June 12 (Reuters) - Swedish bank Nordea <NDA.ST> has appointed David Hellemann as the new head of its Banking Denmark division, as the current manager Anders Jensen will leave the company for a new job at Danish mortgage lender Nykredit [FRNYKR.UL].

Hellemann, 43, currently the top civil servant at the Danish Finance Ministry, will take up the new job on August 6, Nordea said in a press release.